# Prisma multiSchema — module schema discipline

Authored 2026-05-28 as companion to umbraculum-dev
[RFC-0010](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/rfcs/0010-platform-brewery-postgres-schema-split.md)
and [`platform-brewery-postgres-schema-split.md`](https://github.com/umbraculum-dev/umbraculum-dev/blob/master/docs/design/platform-brewery-postgres-schema-split.md).

## Layout (committed)

| Postgres schema | Owner |
|-----------------|-------|
| `platform` | Horizontal: auth, workspace, billing, ads, AI consultant, integrations |
| `brewery` | Tier-6 brewery vertical domain tables |
| `<code>` | Canonical modules (`automation`, `pim`, `mrp`, `crp`, …) |
| `rendering` | Platform rendering jobs |
| `ai`, `reporting` | SQL-only (outside Prisma `datasource.schemas`) |

**Do not** add new Prisma-managed models to `public`.

## `registerModule({ prismaSchema })`

- Canonical modules and tier-6 verticals **must** set `prismaSchema` to the Postgres schema name (usually the module `code`).
- Example: `registerBreweryModule` → `prismaSchema: "brewery"`.
- Platform horizontal models are **not** registered via `registerModule`; they live in `platform.*` only.

## Cross-schema `@relation`

Allowed when both schemas are listed in `datasource db { schemas = [...] }`.
Shipped examples: `brewery.*` → `platform.Workspace`; `automation.Vessel` → `brewery.EquipmentProfile`.

Prefer app-level UUID FKs only when intentional — document why in the module surface doc.

## Migrations

1. **Backup first:** `pg_dump -Fc` to `backups/` before DDL (see companion runbook §3).
2. **Forward migrations only** — never rewrite applied files under `prisma/migrations/`.
3. Recreate `reporting.*` views when underlying table schemas change.
4. Apply with `DATABASE_URL=$DATABASE_URL_DIRECT npx prisma migrate deploy` in the API container.
5. Run `npx prisma generate` + full API test suite after `schema.prisma` changes.

## New module tables

Greenfield modules get a dedicated Postgres schema from the **first** migration.
Never add module-owned tables to `platform` or `brewery` unless explicitly horizontal/vertical per RFC.
